post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are already [easy to get](https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/drugs-buy-how-easy-buy-ice-cream-takeaway-cocaine-crack-marijuana-a8142191.html).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A change in the law to deny all those who suffer self inflicted physical ill-health or mental trauma, including junkies, free access to the N.H.S., would, or at least should jolt the pleasure seekers out of their surreal world in which they enjoy a ''free ride''."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalising drugs related to date rape could bring the issue further into the public eye, allowing for more widespread education on the topic.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization reduces the danger of overdosing.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Specialists working for the government could provide the necessary education on the subject of responsible substance use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The British Empire went to [war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opium_Wars) because they wanted to trade opium in China. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[New research](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/0269881118806297) on PTSD has shown that MDMA-assisted psychotherapy is an extremely effective treatment.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since adults would prefer the legal market, these people would have to base their entire business on selling to underaged people. This would make it drastically less profitable, as well as easier to expose by police.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The Netherlands' comparably liberal [drug policy](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) has generated positive outcomes."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The cigarette industry suppressed research that demonstrated the carcinogenicity of cigarettes \\([pg. 2](https://www.who.int/tobacco/media/en/TobaccoExplained.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many [deaths](http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-24581947) attributed to ecstasy \\(or MDMA\\) use are actually caused by other, unwanted ingredients.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The highest tax estimates of marijuana legalisation reach[$28 billion](https://taxfoundation.org/marijuana-tax-legalization-federal-revenue/) from federal revenues, business taxes and income taxes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under legalisation, self-injection as a route of administration may be reduced, as safer alternatives become available.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Addictions can lead to improper care of children, relatives, or any person \\(even animals\\) who depends on the user.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A high level of correlation does not indicate which of the variables is the cause and which is the effect. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs deprives criminals of a substantial source of their income. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Chronic cocaine use causes [multiple damaging health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine#Chronic) to the user, combined with an increased tolerance, leading to a snowball effect of deteriorating health.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalized, users could be required to carry safe containers for syringes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The lack of regulation surrounding prescribed opioids was caused by pharmaceutical companies [failing to divulge](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) how addictive opioid painkillers were to the medical community in the 1990s.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Numerous events have an equal impact on moral judgments; This should not be the reason for the ban on drug use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would allow for a boom in the economy as there would be an increased demand, and so more farmers would be required to grow the drugs required.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalisation will at length normalize drug use, which can lead to excess use as with alcohol \\(drinking games, binge drinking\\) which can be far more dangerous when done with hard drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some adults may sell drugs to underaged people to make profit. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2014, [8.7%](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-costs-smoking-idUSKBN0JX2BE20141219) of all healthcare spending in the US was spent on tobacco-related illnesses.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legal sellers will be highly scrutinized and won't want to risk losing their license. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer will benefit all users, while a false sense of safety only applies to a minority. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Such stress might be irrational, especially when it's related to unproblematic drug use. In that case, the psychological stress is the fault of the persons irrational beliefs."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
